  "ideas": {
    "intro": "Ideas for projects, activities, books, games, and more for students with a high level of interest.",
    "terms": [
      {
        "term": 1,
        "title": "Term 1",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "rect7ibymstAxnVWE",
            "term": 1,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] (Bible) Act out a memorable Bible reading from the term.\n[ ] (Old Testament) Use scraps of fabric to sew a simple \"coat (or cape) of many colors\" for a stuffed animal or doll. (Tie dye is another option.)\n[ ] (Old Testament) [Explore the size of Noah's Ark. ](https://arkencounter.com/noahs-ark/size/)\n[ ] (Old Testament) Use scraps of fabric to sew a simple \"coat (or cape) of many colors\" for a stuffed animal or doll. (Tie dye is another option.)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "term": 2,
        "title": "Term 2",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "recnDBaA2xeryrgaM",
            "term": 2,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] (Bible) Create a Bible shoebox diorama using recycled objects, outdoor objects, and/or play figures to go with one of the readings from this term. You can find many ideas on Pinterest for inspiration.\n[ ] (Bible) Explore the [virtual resources](https://www.museumofthebible.org/museum-from-home) at the Museum of the Bible. (Note: a parent should preview.)\n[ ] (New Testament) Share a meal with others such as taking donations to a food bank, taking a meal to a neighbor, or baking cookies for a local fire or police station.\n[ ] (Old Testament) Listen to[ Psalms set to music](https://thepsalmsproject.com/music), or create your own music (you could use piano, rhythm sticks, tambourine, or drum) to accompany one of the Psalms you read this term."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "term": 3,
        "title": "Term 3",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "reciJumsFErXSUfbw",
            "term": 3,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] (New Testament) Spend time fishing as a family and try to name all the times fishing or fish are mentioned in this term's readings.\n[ ] (New Testament) [Create a \"Resurrection Garden.\" (These can also be used as centerpieces for Easter dinner.)](https://seedskidsworship.com/resurrection-garden/)\n[ ] (Bible) Share a meal with others such as taking donations to a food bank, taking a meal to a neighbor, or baking cookies for a local fire or police station."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
